Sometimes we buy on impulse and this does not apply…in economics, we assume consumers are rational most of the time

When you are willing to pay $30 for a shirt, it must be that the benefit you get from the shirt, is greater than the benefit you get from keeping the money. Otherwise you would not have made the exchange.
You reveal that the shirt’s dollar “value” to you is equal (or higher) than $30
